---
import CaseStudy from '../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---
<CaseStudy
  title="About — Cansu Tecimer"
  description="About Cansu Tecimer — product and UX design manager based in Berlin."
>

  <section class="hero container">
    <p class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> About</p>
    <h1 class="display">Hi, I'm <em>Cansu</em>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Product designer and UX leader in Berlin. After a decade in design leadership roles at HelloFresh and GetYourGuide, I'm back in the weeds, building a cycling coaching app from the ground up.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="bento container">
    <div class="bento-item bento-lg">
      <img src="/images/Cansu-Meetup.jpg" alt="Cansu at a design meetup" />
    </div>
    <div class="bento-item">
      <img src="/images/Cansu-Fun.jpg" alt="Cansu having fun" />
    </div>
    <div class="bento-item">
      <img src="/images/Cansu-Travel.jpg" alt="Cansu travelling" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story container">
    <div class="story-grid">
      <aside class="story-label">
        <span class="index">01</span>
        <h2>About me</h2>
      </aside>
      <div class="story-body">
        <p class="first-para">I'm a product designer and UX leader, currently based in Berlin. I've previously lived in Istanbul, Ankara, Malatya, Louisville, and San Francisco, and hopefully I'll keep adding to the list.</p>
        <p>I spent the last 10 years in high-growth companies, mostly in leadership roles. At HelloFresh, I joined as the second designer and later became Head of UX, building the design organization from the ground up and leading it through rapid growth and IPO. At GetYourGuide, I worked as a Senior UX Manager, focusing on growth, retention, and design systems, and helping teams align on larger initiatives.</p>
        <p>More recently, I wanted to get closer to the craft again and started building my own company with an engineering partner who's also an avid cyclist, which turns out to be pretty essential when your product is a cycling coaching app. I'm currently working on Steady, taking it from 0 to 1 across product, design, marketing, emails, and some frontend. It's been very hands-on, and I've really enjoyed building something from scratch.</p>
        <p>Alongside that, I mentor designers on ADPList, which taps into what I've always liked about leadership: helping people think through problems and grow in their careers.</p>
        <p>Outside of work, I've been getting into mystery books, cooking more, and continuing my ongoing obsession with good food, which Berlin makes very easy. I also move a lot. Long walks, spinning, Pilates, strength — partly because I enjoy it and partly because it's the only reliable way I've found to quiet my head.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story container">
    <div class="story-grid">
      <aside class="story-label">
        <span class="index">02</span>
        <h2>Experience</h2>
      </aside>
      <div class="story-body">
        <ol class="experience-list">
          <li>
            <span class="experience-date">2026 — Present</span>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Co-founder &amp; Designer — Steady</h3>
            <p>Co-founded Steady, building and designing the product from the ground up.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="experience-date">2019 — 2024</span>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Senior UX Manager — GetYourGuide</h3>
            <p>Led UX for the Growth Product Group — audience growth, engagement, and the early discovery experience of travelers. Partnered with the Director of Product on strategy, grew the UX team, and secured resourcing for Compass, GetYourGuide's design system.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="experience-date">2017 — 2018</span>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Head of UX — HelloFresh</h3>
            <p>Led the design team across HelloFresh's digital platforms, growing it from 2 to 14 and setting up structures for career growth and quality of output. Sponsored retention experiments (+16% orders per customer) and a design system to lift designer and developer efficiency.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="experience-date">2015 — 2017</span>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Product Designer — HelloFresh</h3>
            <p>Worked on large-scale projects — the HelloFresh loyalty program, US wine club, and revamp of the account area. Led research across multiple markets and wove insights into the design workflow.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="experience-date">2013 — 2015</span>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Senior Interaction Designer — Monitise</h3>
            <p>Sole interaction designer on Ziraat Bank's mobile app, and design lead on projects for clients like RBS and Visa. Ran user research and usability studies, and owned the design track on long- and short-term engagements.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="experience-date">2013</span>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">User Experience Designer — Weather Underground</h3>
            <p>Worked with PM, UI designer, developers, and meteorologists to ship site-wide weather alerts and lift sign-up rates for the PWS program.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="experience-date">2011</span>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Graduate Researcher — Intel × CCA</h3>
            <p>Conceptualized new products and prototyped with Processing, Arduino, and Lego Mindstorms as part of Intel's future-technologies program.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="experience-date">2008</span>
            <h3 class="sub-heading">Industrial Product Designer — FYM Creative Group</h3>
            <p>Lead designer on exhibition stands, product displays, and event venues.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story container">
    <div class="story-grid">
      <aside class="story-label">
        <span class="index">03</span>
        <h2>Ways to work together</h2>
      </aside>
      <div class="story-body">
        <p class="first-para">I work with teams as an embedded design partner. The founding designer for a team shaping a product, or the senior hire who builds out a design practice for a team past zero-to-one. I fill the design gap, build alongside the team, and hand it off when they're ready to take it on.</p>
        <div class="engagement-grid">
          <article class="engagement-card">
            <p class="engagement-tag">Shaping products</p>
            <h3>Embedded "founding" designer</h3>
            <p class="engagement-who">For founders and small teams shaping a product, I'll be the design and product partner.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Hands-on product thinking and UX, end-to-end when needed</li>
              <li>Research, problem framing, flow design, MVPs</li>
              <li>Close partnership with engineering to ship and learn fast</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="engagement-card">
            <p class="engagement-tag">Shaping teams</p>
            <h3>Fractional design leadership</h3>
            <p class="engagement-who">For teams further along, I take on fractional leadership.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Hands-on design support if needed</li>
              <li>Building the design function (hiring, building processes, etc.)</li>
              <li>Partnering with PM and engineering to define ways of working</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story container">
    <div class="story-grid">
      <aside class="story-label">
        <span class="index">04</span>
        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      </aside>
      <div class="story-body">
        <p class="first-para">I'm always happy to chat — about projects, design, managing design teams, or where our industry is headed.</p>
        <p><a href="mailto:cansutecimer@gmail.com" class="contact-link">cansutecimer@gmail.com</a> · <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/cansu-tecimer-a3458b47/" class="contact-link">LinkedIn</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</CaseStudy>
